main event: A witness observed a circular, luminous object hovering over a wooded area near Salem, Virginia on April 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as being circular in shape and luminous.
Five witnesses reported observing the object, which hovered over the area for an undetermined length of time before disappearing.
One photograph of the object was obtained.
No sound or means of propulsion was reported.
The case was classified as unidentified and remained open for further investigation.
